doc.after: The Grand Forks Herald is the major daily newspaper serving Grand Forks[78] and is also the second most widely circulated newspaper in North Dakota with a daily circulation of around 31,000.[79] The Exponent is a weekly newspaper published in East Grand Forks, Minnesota.[80] The University of North Dakota also has its own student-published newspaper called The Dakota Student, which is published twice weekly during the school year.[81]
